U.S. Newsprint Use
   Rose 0.4% Last Month
The association said newsprint consumption by U.S. daily
newspapers fell 0.9% in December to 725,055 metric tons from
731,674 metric tons a year earlier. In the full year, daily
newspapers' newsprint consumption fell 6.5% to 8,311,441
metric tons from 8,893,495 metric tons.
   Newsprint inventories of newspapers in the association's
statistical sample averaged a 45-day supply in December
compared with a 43-day supply a year ago.
   The association said Canadian newsprint mills operated at
74% of rated capacity in December and 87% in the full year,
while U.S. newsprint mills operated at 96.3% of rated
capacity in December and 95.5% in the full year.